The paper discusses the use of Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT) for billing and charging services for Electric Autonomous Vehicles (EAVs). This topic falls under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it involves ensuring the security and privacy of users during transactions. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture and framework for charging and billing, which could fall under the categories of Control Systems (cs.CY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of Machine-to-Machine (M2M) transactions, which could fall under the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
